# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# GoDo App — API Keys & Environment Variables
# Copy this file to .env.local and fill in your keys.
# NEVER commit .env.local to git.
# Add any combination — the app uses whichever keys are present.
# Last updated: April 2026
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────


# ═════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# SECTION 1: EVENTS (Concerts, Shows, Festivals, Sports, Tickets)
# ═════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

# ── TICKETMASTER Discovery API ───────────────────────────────────────────────
# What: Concerts, sports, theater, family events — massive US coverage.
#       Returns venue lat/lng, price ranges, dates, genres.
# NYC coverage: Excellent. Best for ticketed major events.
# Free tier: 5,000 calls/day, 5 req/sec. No credit card required.
# Sign-up: https://developer.ticketmaster.com
# Env var convention: VITE_TICKETMASTER_API_KEY
VITE_TICKETMASTER_API_KEY=your_ticketmaster_key_here

# ── SEATGEEK Platform API ────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# What: Concerts, sports, broadway, comedy — includes "deal score" for tickets.
#       Great discovery scores, real avg/low/high prices per event.
# NYC coverage: Excellent. Strong Broadway + sports data.
# Free tier: Free public Client ID, no hard published limit.
#            ~500 events per call with pagination. No credit card required.
# Sign-up: https://seatgeek.com/build  (takes ~2 minutes)
# Env var convention: VITE_SEATGEEK_CLIENT_ID
VITE_SEATGEEK_CLIENT_ID=your_seatgeek_client_id_here

# ── EVENTBRITE API ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# What: Community events, festivals, classes, conferences, free events.
#       Returns venue, price, organizer, attendee count.
# NYC coverage: Very good for grassroots/community events.
# Free tier: 1,000 calls/hour per token, 48,000/day. No credit card required.
# NOTE: As of 2025, Eventbrite has restricted some API access. Monitor status.
# Sign-up: https://www.eventbrite.com/platform/api
# Env var convention: VITE_EVENTBRITE_API_KEY
VITE_EVENTBRITE_API_KEY=your_eventbrite_key_here

# ── BANDSINTOWN API ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# What: Live music events for specific artists, tour dates, venues.
#       Search by artist name or location. Returns upcoming concert data.
# NYC coverage: Good for indie/local music scenes.
# Free tier: Free public API, requires app_id (your app name as identifier).
#            No formal rate limit published. No credit card required.
# Sign-up: https://artists.bandsintown.com/bandsintown-api
#           OR via SwaggerHub developer account
# Env var convention: VITE_BANDSINTOWN_APP_ID
VITE_BANDSINTOWN_APP_ID=your_app_name_here

# ── SONGKICK API ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# What: Concerts, festivals, and tours — biggest live music DB (6M+ events).
#       Search by metro area, artist, or venue.
# NYC coverage: Excellent — huge NYC metro area dataset.
# Free tier: Free tier exists but NEW API KEY APPLICATIONS PAUSED as of 2025.
#            Contact partnerships@songkick.com for business access.
# Sign-up: https://www.songkick.com/developer  (check current availability)
# Env var convention: VITE_SONGKICK_API_KEY
VITE_SONGKICK_API_KEY=your_songkick_key_here

# ── PREDICTHQ Events Intelligence API ───────────────────────────────────────
# What: Aggregated events across 19 categories: sports, concerts, conferences,
#       festivals, expos, community events, school holidays, etc.
#       Includes attendance predictions and demand impact scores.
# NYC coverage: Excellent — NYC-specific filters available.
# Free tier: 14-day full trial, then Free Plan (limited calls/month).
#            Paid plans start at $500/year. Credit card likely required.
# Sign-up: https://www.predicthq.com/api-key-request
# Env var convention: VITE_PREDICTHQ_ACCESS_TOKEN
VITE_PREDICTHQ_ACCESS_TOKEN=your_predicthq_token_here

# ── SERPAPI — Google Events Results API ─────────────────────────────────────
# What: Scrapes Google's "Events" SERP for any city/query.
#       Returns event title, date, venue, description, ticket links, thumbnail.
# NYC coverage: Excellent — mirrors what Google shows for "events in NYC".
# Free tier: 250 searches/month. 50 req/hour throughput. No credit card needed.
# Sign-up: https://serpapi.com/users/sign_up
# Docs: https://serpapi.com/google-events-api
# Env var convention: VITE_SERPAPI_KEY
VITE_SERPAPI_KEY=your_serpapi_key_here

# ── DICE.FM API ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# What: Underground clubs, electronic music, comedy, talks — curated nightlife.
#       GraphQL API (Ticket Holders API) for partners.
# NYC coverage: Good for indie/electronic/underground events.
# Free tier: No public free tier. Partner/promoter access only.
#            Contact: https://dice.fm/partners  OR  https://partners.dice.fm
# NOTE: No public developer key. Requires partnership agreement.
# Env var convention: VITE_DICE_API_TOKEN
# VITE_DICE_API_TOKEN=your_dice_token_here

# NOTE — DEAD/PAUSED APIs in the events category:
# Eventful: SHUT DOWN in late 2020. Do not use.
# Do212: No public API available.
# Hidden City NYC: No API; editorial content site only.
# TimeOut: No public developer API available (editorial site only).
# Patch.com: Hyperlocal events calendar but no public REST API for developers.
# Resident Advisor (RA): No official public API. Use third-party scrapers or
#   RA Pro for promoters: https://pro.ra.co/listing


# ═════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# SECTION 2: RESTAURANTS, BARS & FOOD
# ═════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

# ── YELP FUSION / PLACES API ─────────────────────────────────────────────────
# What: Restaurants, bars, nightlife, services — real star ratings & reviews.
#       Price tier ($-$$$), hours, photos, categories, coordinates.
# NYC coverage: Excellent. Best restaurant discovery coverage in NYC.
# Free tier: 30-day free trial (5,000 calls). After trial: PAID ONLY.
#            Starter plan: ~$7.99 per 1,000 calls. Credit card required.
# Sign-up: https://www.yelp.com/developers/v3/manage_app
# NOTE: Requires proxy (CORS blocked client-side). See vite.config.ts.
# Env var convention: VITE_YELP_API_KEY
VITE_YELP_API_KEY=your_yelp_key_here

# ── FOURSQUARE Places API v3 ─────────────────────────────────────────────────
# What: 100M+ global POIs — restaurants, parks, attractions, gyms, museums.
#       Includes ratings (0-10), price tier, hours, categories, photos.
# NYC coverage: Excellent. Deep NYC POI database.
# Free tier: 10,000 calls/month to Pro endpoints. No credit card required
#            to start. Premium endpoints (photos, tips) cost extra.
# Sign-up: https://location.foursquare.com/developer/
# Env var convention: VITE_FOURSQUARE_API_KEY
VITE_FOURSQUARE_API_KEY=your_foursquare_key_here

# ── OPENTABLE API ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# What: Restaurant reservation availability, dining info, OpenTable listings.
#       Real-time table availability + restaurant metadata.
# NYC coverage: Excellent. Most NYC restaurants use OpenTable.
# Free tier: Partner/affiliate program only. 3-4 week approval process.
# Sign-up: https://dev.opentable.com  (apply as affiliate partner)
# NOTE: Not a self-serve API — requires manual application and approval.
# Env var convention: VITE_OPENTABLE_API_KEY
# VITE_OPENTABLE_API_KEY=your_opentable_key_here

# ── RESY API ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# What: Restaurant reservation platform — high-end NYC restaurants heavily use
#       Resy. Real-time availability, restaurant profiles, neighborhood data.
# NYC coverage: Excellent for upscale/trendy NYC dining.
# Free tier: No official public API. Resy uses an unofficial/private API.
#            Some developers reverse-engineer it; no ToS-safe public key.
# NOTE: No public developer program as of 2026.
# Sign-up: https://resy.com/resyos/integrations/ (for restaurant operators only)
# Env var convention: VITE_RESY_API_KEY
# VITE_RESY_API_KEY=your_resy_key_here

# ── ZOMATO / BLINKIT API ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# What: Restaurant listings, menus, reviews, ratings globally.
#       (Urbanspoon was acquired by Zomato in 2014.)
# NYC coverage: Limited compared to Yelp — Zomato pivoted to India delivery.
# Free tier: 1,000 calls/day. Requires formal developer approval.
# Sign-up: https://www.zomato.com/developer/integration/
# NOTE: Public API largely deprecated in US. Mainly useful for global coverage.
# Env var convention: VITE_ZOMATO_API_KEY
# VITE_ZOMATO_API_KEY=your_zomato_key_here

# NOTE — No public API available:
# The Infatuation: Editorial site; no public API.


# ═════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# SECTION 3: MAPS, PLACES & GEOCODING
# ═════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

# ── GOOGLE PLACES API (New) ──────────────────────────────────────────────────
# What: Places Search, Nearby Search, Place Details, Photos, Reviews.
#       Most comprehensive POI database on Earth. Includes hours, busy times.
# NYC coverage: Exceptional — the gold standard for POI data.
# Free tier: 10,000 calls/month per SKU (Essentials tier). Credit card REQUIRED
#            to enable billing (even for free tier). Worth it for data quality.
# Sign-up: https://console.cloud.google.com/google/maps-apis/overview
# Env var convention: VITE_GOOGLE_PLACES_API_KEY
VITE_GOOGLE_PLACES_API_KEY=your_google_places_key_here

# ── MAPBOX API ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# What: Map tiles, Geocoding (100K req/month free), Search Box (POI search),
#       Navigation, Isochrones. 170M+ global POIs via Search Box API.
# NYC coverage: Excellent for mapping and geocoding.
# Free tier: 100,000 geocoding requests/month. 50,000 map loads/month.
#            No credit card required to start.
# Sign-up: https://account.mapbox.com/auth/signup/
# Env var convention: VITE_MAPBOX_TOKEN
VITE_MAPBOX_TOKEN=your_mapbox_public_token_here

# ── HERE Maps / Places API ───────────────────────────────────────────────────
# What: Geocoding, Reverse Geocoding, Places Search, Routing.
#       250,000 free transactions/month — generous vs Google.
# NYC coverage: Very good. Enterprise-grade location data.
# Free tier: 1,000 req/day (no card) OR 30,000 req/month (with card).
#            Some sources say 250,000/month — verify on signup.
# Sign-up: https://developer.here.com/sign-up
# Env var convention: VITE_HERE_API_KEY
VITE_HERE_API_KEY=your_here_api_key_here

# ── OPENSTREETMAP — Overpass API ─────────────────────────────────────────────
# What: Community-sourced POI data — restaurants, parks, museums, transit.
#       Query by bounding box, tags (amenity=restaurant, leisure=park, etc).
# NYC coverage: Very good for OSM-tagged locations. Community maintained.
# Free tier: Completely FREE. No API key required. Public endpoint.
#            Rate limit: be respectful — not for high-volume production use.
# Endpoint: https://overpass-api.de/api/interpreter
# Sign-up: None required.
# Env var convention: N/A (no key needed)
# VITE_OVERPASS_ENDPOINT=https://overpass-api.de/api/interpreter


# ═════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# SECTION 4: NYC GOVERNMENT / OPEN DATA APIs
# (All free, most require only an optional app token for higher rate limits)
# ═════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

# ── NYC OPEN DATA — Socrata / SODA API ──────────────────────────────────────
# What: ~23,000 datasets from NYC agencies. Key datasets for GoDo:
#   - Parks Special Events: https://data.cityofnewyork.us/resource/6v4b-5gp4.json
#     (fitness, sports, movies, concerts in parks — one-off public events)
#   - Restaurant Inspections (DOHMH): https://data.cityofnewyork.us/resource/43nn-pn8j.json
#     (grades, scores, violations — great for food safety overlay)
#   - NYC Events Calendar (nyc.gov): https://api-portal.nyc.gov (see below)
#   - 311 Service Requests: https://data.cityofnewyork.us/resource/erm2-nwe9.json
#   - Parks Properties: https://data.cityofnewyork.us/resource/enfh-gkve.json
#   - Cultural Organizations: https://data.cityofnewyork.us/resource/u35m-9t32.json
# NYC coverage: Hyper-local NYC government data. Unmatched for official data.
# Free tier: FREE. No key needed for basic queries (up to 1,000 rows/request).
#            With an app token: much higher rate limits (1,000 req/hour).
# Sign-up for app token: https://data.cityofnewyork.us/profile/app_tokens
# Env var convention: VITE_NYC_OPEN_DATA_APP_TOKEN
VITE_NYC_OPEN_DATA_APP_TOKEN=your_nyc_open_data_token_here

# ── NYC GOV EVENTS CALENDAR API ──────────────────────────────────────────────
# What: Official NYC government-sponsored events — same data as nyc.gov
#       "Find Local Events" module. City agency events, public programs.
# NYC coverage: 100% NYC-specific. Official city events only.
# Free tier: FREE with developer key. Signup via NYC Developer Portal.
# Sign-up: https://api-portal.nyc.gov/signup
# Env var convention: VITE_NYC_GOV_EVENTS_KEY
VITE_NYC_GOV_EVENTS_KEY=your_nyc_gov_events_key_here

# ── NYC GEOCLIENT API ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# What: NYC-specific geocoding using the city's official Geosupport system.
#       Turns NYC addresses into coordinates + neighborhood/borough data.
#       Supports address, intersection, blockface lookups.
# NYC coverage: NYC addresses only — most accurate geocoder for NYC.
# Free tier: FREE. Approval may take a few days (email notification on approval).
# Sign-up: https://developer.cityofnewyork.us/api/geoclient-api
# Env var convention: VITE_NYC_GEOCLIENT_APP_ID + VITE_NYC_GEOCLIENT_APP_KEY
VITE_NYC_GEOCLIENT_APP_ID=your_geoclient_app_id_here
VITE_NYC_GEOCLIENT_APP_KEY=your_geoclient_app_key_here

# ── 511NY TRANSIT API ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# What: Real-time NYC/NY transit data — traffic, incidents, roadwork, cameras.
#       Also covers MTA alerts and events affecting transportation.
# NYC coverage: NYC + metro region transportation data.
# Free tier: FREE. Rate limited to 10 calls per 60 seconds.
#            Requires application with brief description of use.
# Sign-up: https://511ny.org/developers/resources
# Env var convention: VITE_511NY_API_KEY
VITE_511NY_API_KEY=your_511ny_key_here

# ── MTA Real-Time GTFS Feeds ─────────────────────────────────────────────────
# What: Real-time NYC subway/bus positions, service alerts, trip updates.
#       GTFS-RT format (Protocol Buffers). Free as of v2.0.0.
# NYC coverage: All NYC subway lines, buses, LIRR, Metro-North.
# Free tier: COMPLETELY FREE. No API key required as of 2024 update.
# Sign-up: None — register at https://new.mta.info/developers for notifications.
# Endpoints:
#   Subway: https://api-endpoint.mta.info/Dataservice/mtagtfsfeeds/nyct%2Fgtfs
#   Bus: https://bustime.mta.info/api/siri/...
#   Alerts: https://api-endpoint.mta.info/Dataservice/mtagtfsfeeds/camsys%2Fall-alerts
# Env var convention: N/A (no key required) or VITE_MTA_API_KEY if you register
# VITE_MTA_API_KEY=your_mta_key_here


# ═════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# SECTION 5: MUSEUMS & CULTURAL INSTITUTIONS
# ═════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

# ── THE MET (Metropolitan Museum of Art) Collection API ──────────────────────
# What: 470,000+ artworks, exhibition data, high-res public domain images.
#       Search by department, keyword, date, artist, medium.
# NYC coverage: 100% NYC — The Met's full collection.
# Free tier: COMPLETELY FREE. No API key required. Public REST API.
# Docs: https://metmuseum.github.io/
# Endpoint: https://collectionapi.metmuseum.org/public/collection/v1/
# Sign-up: None required.
# Env var convention: N/A (no key needed)
# VITE_MET_API_BASE=https://collectionapi.metmuseum.org/public/collection/v1

# ── BROOKLYN MUSEUM Collection API ──────────────────────────────────────────
# What: Brooklyn Museum's full art collection — objects, images, exhibitions.
#       Returns structured data and image links.
# NYC coverage: 100% NYC — Brooklyn Museum's collection.
# Free tier: Free with API key. Non-commercial use. No credit card required.
# Sign-up: https://www.brooklynmuseum.org/opencollection/api/register
# Env var convention: VITE_BROOKLYN_MUSEUM_API_KEY
VITE_BROOKLYN_MUSEUM_API_KEY=your_brooklyn_museum_key_here

# ── NYPL Digital Collections API ─────────────────────────────────────────────
# What: 1M+ digitized objects — photos, maps, manuscripts, menus, art.
#       NYC cultural history archive. Search, browse hierarchically.
# NYC coverage: Exceptional NYC historical/cultural content.
# Free tier: FREE with token. 10,000 req/day. No credit card required.
# DEPRECATION WARNING: Being deprecated as of August 1, 2026.
#   Contact digitaldam@nypl.org for future access options.
# Sign-up: https://api.repo.nypl.org/ (while still active)
# Env var convention: VITE_NYPL_API_TOKEN
VITE_NYPL_API_TOKEN=your_nypl_token_here


# ═════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# SECTION 6: PARKS & OUTDOOR ACTIVITIES
# ═════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

# NYC Parks data is best accessed via the NYC Open Data token above.
# Key Parks datasets (no separate key needed — use VITE_NYC_OPEN_DATA_APP_TOKEN):
#
#   Parks Special Events (fitness, concerts, movies in parks):
#     https://data.cityofnewyork.us/resource/6v4b-5gp4.json
#
#   Parks Properties (all 1,700+ NYC parks with geometry):
#     https://data.cityofnewyork.us/resource/enfh-gkve.json
#
#   Parks Permit Areas (permitted event spaces):
#     https://data.cityofnewyork.us/resource/gc68-nd28.json
#
#   Parks Programs (recurring events like fitness classes, workshops):
#     https://data.cityofnewyork.us/resource/4ufh-mxqs.json
#
# NYC Parks Website (no API but scrape-friendly):
#   https://www.nycgovparks.org/events


# ═════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# SECTION 7: COMMUNITY EVENTS & SOCIAL
# ═════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

# ── MEETUP API (GraphQL) ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# What: Community meetups — tech, fitness, social, hobby groups.
#       NYC has thousands of active Meetup groups across all interests.
# NYC coverage: Excellent for community/interest-based events.
# Free tier: NO FREE TIER. Requires active Meetup Pro subscription ($30+/mo).
#            OAuth consumer creation requires Pro membership.
# Sign-up: https://www.meetup.com/graphql/ (Pro members only)
# NOTE: Not viable for indie developers on free plan.
# Env var convention: VITE_MEETUP_CLIENT_ID + VITE_MEETUP_CLIENT_SECRET
# VITE_MEETUP_CLIENT_ID=your_meetup_client_id_here
# VITE_MEETUP_CLIENT_SECRET=your_meetup_client_secret_here

# ── TRIPADVISOR Content API ──────────────────────────────────────────────────
# What: Attraction listings, restaurant data, reviews, photos, ratings.
#       Strong for tourist-facing venues — museums, tours, experiences.
# NYC coverage: Excellent for popular attractions and restaurants.
# Free tier: 5,000 calls/month free. Credit card REQUIRED (for overage billing).
#            Intended for consumer-facing (B2C) websites with real traffic.
# Sign-up: https://developer-tripadvisor.com/content-api/
# Env var convention: VITE_TRIPADVISOR_API_KEY
VITE_TRIPADVISOR_API_KEY=your_tripadvisor_key_here


# ═════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# SECTION 8: NIGHTLIFE & MUSIC DISCOVERY
# ═════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

# ── RESIDENT ADVISOR (RA) ────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# No official public API. Data accessible only via:
#   - Third-party scrapers on Apify: https://apify.com/augeas/resident-advisor
#   - RA Pro for promoters: https://pro.ra.co (listing management only)
# For nightlife/electronic music events, use Dice.fm or Bandsintown instead.

# ── DICE.FM ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# See SECTION 1 above (VITE_DICE_API_TOKEN)
# Partner GraphQL API: https://partners-endpoint.dice.fm/graphql/docs/

# ── BANDSINTOWN ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# See SECTION 1 above (VITE_BANDSINTOWN_APP_ID)


# ═════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# SECTION 9: TRANSIT & ACCESSIBILITY
# ═════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

# See SECTION 4:
#   - 511NY API (VITE_511NY_API_KEY) — traffic, incidents, transit events
#   - MTA GTFS Feeds (no key) — real-time subway/bus
#
# Additional transit resources (no API key needed):
#   NYC Subway Entrances/Exits dataset:
#     https://data.cityofnewyork.us/resource/drh3-e2fd.json
#   Bike Share (Citi Bike GBFS feed — free, no key):
#     https://gbfs.citibikenyc.com/gbfs/en/station_information.json
#   Ferry Schedules (NYC Ferry — GTFS feed):
#     https://www.ferry.nyc/routes-and-schedules/
#   Accessible facilities (ADA compliant stations):
#     https://data.cityofnewyork.us/resource/nnm4-nnh7.json


# ═════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# SECTION 10: QUICK-REFERENCE — FREE TIER SUMMARY
# ═════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
#
# KEY: [CC] = credit card required  [~CC] = may ask for CC  [FREE] = no CC
#
# ALREADY INTEGRATED:
#  Ticketmaster        5,000/day       [FREE]  events, concerts, sports
#  SeatGeek            unlimited*      [FREE]  concerts, broadway, sports
#  Eventbrite          48,000/day      [FREE]  community events, free events
#  Yelp Fusion         30-day trial    [CC]    restaurants, bars, ratings
#  Foursquare v3       10,000/month    [FREE]  places, parks, attractions
#
# HIGH PRIORITY TO ADD:
#  NYC Open Data (SODA) unlimited*    [FREE]  parks events, inspections, govt
#  NYC Gov Events API  unlimited*     [FREE]  official city events
#  MET Museum API      unlimited      [FREE]  museum collections & info
#  Google Places (New) 10,000/month   [CC]    best POI data, required for scale
#  Mapbox              100,000/month  [FREE]  maps, geocoding, POI search
#  Bandsintown         generous       [FREE]  live music, concerts
#  SerpApi             250/month      [FREE]  Google Events scraping
#  Brooklyn Museum     unlimited*     [FREE]  museum, exhibitions
#
# MEDIUM PRIORITY:
#  HERE Maps           250,000/month  [~CC]   geocoding, places, routing
#  TripAdvisor Content 5,000/month    [CC]    attractions, tourist venues
#  NYPL Collections    10,000/day     [FREE]  historical NYC content
#  NYC Geoclient       unlimited*     [FREE]  NYC address geocoding
#  511NY               10/60sec       [FREE]  transit & traffic events
#  MTA GTFS            unlimited      [FREE]  real-time subway/bus
#  Citi Bike GBFS      unlimited      [FREE]  bike share station data
#
# LOWER PRIORITY / LIMITED ACCESS:
#  Meetup              none           [PAID]  requires Pro subscription $30+/mo
#  OpenTable           partner only   [APPLY] 3-4 week approval
#  PredictHQ           14-day trial   [CC?]   event demand intelligence $500/yr
#  Songkick            PAUSED         [N/A]   new keys paused — contact them
#  Dice.fm             partner only   [APPLY] nightlife/underground events
#
# NO PUBLIC API (use alternative):
#  Resident Advisor    no public API  —       use Dice.fm or Bandsintown
#  TimeOut NYC         no API         —       editorial only
#  Patch.com           no public API  —       hyperlocal news, no dev program
#  Resy                no public API  —       restaurant operators only
#  The Infatuation     no API         —       editorial only
#  Hidden City NYC     no API         —       editorial only
#  Do212               no API         —       editorial only
#  Zomato (US)         deprecated     —       US data largely gone
#  Eventful            SHUT DOWN      —       closed 2020
#
# * "unlimited" means no hard cap but fair use / throttling applies
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
